Apart from acting, Kumar has worked as a [[Stunt performer|stunt actor]]; he has often performed many dangerous stunts in his films, which has earned him the sobriquet "Indian [[Jackie Chan]]".<ref name="Chan">{{cite news|title=Akshay Kumar meets Jackie Chan in Hong Kong|date=20 May 2004 |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/2004/05/20/1112/index.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081210042549/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/2004/05/20/1112/index.html |archivedate=10 December 2008|accessdate=11 April 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Mahipal|first=Nikita|url=http://www.koimoi.com/box-office/will-akshay-kumar-s-100th-film-make-100-crores/|title=Will Akshay Kumar's 100th Film Make 100 Crores?|publisher=[[Koimoi]]|date=19 July 2012|accessdate=31 July 2014}}</ref> In 2008, he hosted the show ''[[Fear Factor: Khatron Ke Khiladi]]''. In 2009, he founded the [[Hari Om Entertainment]] production company<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-10-09/news-interviews/28090093_1_akshay-kumar-producer-taare-zameen-par |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120714220114/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-10-09/news-interviews/28090093_1_akshay-kumar-producer-taare-zameen-par |url-status=dead |archive-date=14 July 2012 |title=Main bhi producer!|date=9 October 2009|work=[[The Times of India]]|publisher=[[The Times Group]]|accessdate=18 November 2010}}</ref> and [[Grazing Goat Pictures]] production company in 2012. In 2014, Kumar launched the TV reality show ''[[Dare 2 Dance]]''. He also owns the team Khalsa Warriors in the [[World Kabaddi League]]. {{as of|2019|3=|df=}}, Kumar was on the ''[[Forbes]]'' list of the highest paid entertainers in the world,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/celebrities/|title=The Celebrity 100: The World's Highest-Paid Entertainers 2019|website=Forbes|accessdate=11 March 2020}}</ref> and he was the highest paid in India.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.livemint.com/industry/media/akshay-kumar-only-bollywood-star-in-forbes-highest-paid-celebrities-list/amp-1562841295933.html | title=Akshay Kumar only Bollywood star in Forbes highest paid celebrities list| date=11 July 2019}}</ref>

Sometime during or after the [[2011 Canadian federal election]], the [[Conservative Party (Canada)|Conservative]] government there granted Canadian citizenship to Kumar by invoking a little-known law which allowed circumventing the usual residency requirement for Canadian immigrants.<ref name=National-Post-21-May-2019/>  According to a former Conservative Party minister, [[Tony Clement]], the citizenship was awarded in return for Kumar's offer of putting his "star power to use to advance Canada-Indian relations," and Canada's "trade relations, commercial relations, in the movie sector, in the tourism sector."<ref name=National-Post-21-May-2019/>  In 2008, the [[University of Windsor]] conferred an honorary Doctorate on Kumar in recognition of his contribution to Indian cinema. In 2009, he was awarded the [[Padma Shri]] by the [[Government of India]]. In 2011, [[The Asian Awards]] honoured Kumar for his outstanding achievement in cinema.

== Early life and background ==
Kumar was born in [[Amritsar]], [[Punjab, India|Punjab]], India,<ref name=birth /> to Hari Om Bhatia and Aruna Bhatia in a [[Punjabis|Punjabi]] family.<ref name="HTMKhalid"/><ref name="25years">{{cite web|author=Verma, Sukanya|title=40 things you didn't know about Akki|date=5 September 2007 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/sep/05akshay.htm|publisher=[[Rediff.com]]|accessdate=14 March 2008| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080219044744/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/sep/05akshay.htm| archivedate= 19 February 2008}}</ref> His father was an army officer.<ref>{{cite news|author1=Ritika Handoo|title=Lesser known facts about Akshay Kumar|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/celebrity/lesser-known-facts-about-akshay-kumar_1668704.html|accessdate=5 May 2016|work=Zee News|date=8 September 2015}}</ref> From a young age, Kumar was very interested in sports. His father too enjoyed wrestling. He lived and grew up in Delhi's [[Chandni Chowk]] and later he moved to [[Mumbai|Bombay]] (present-day Mumbai) when his father left Army to become an accountant with [[UNICEF]].<ref name="rstv">{{cite news |last1=S |first1=Irfan |title=Guftagoo with Akshay Kumar |publisher=Rajya Sabha TV |date=3 June 2014}}</ref> Soon, his sister was born and the family lived in [[Guru Tegh Bahadur Nagar|Koliwada]], a Punjabi dominated area of Central Bombay.<ref name="HTMKhalid">{{cite news|last1=Mohammad|first1=Khalid|title=Akshay Kumar is a Punjabi by nature|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/news-feed/entertainment/akshay-kumar-is-a-punjabi-by-nature/article1-211213.aspx|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|accessdate=17 June 2014|location=Mumbai|date=22 March 2007|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131225000554/http://www.hindustantimes.com/News-Feed/Entertainment/Akshay-Kumar-is-a-Punjabi-by-nature/Article1-211213.aspx|archivedate=25 December 2013}}</ref> 

He received his school education from [[Don Bosco High School, Matunga]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Notable Alumni {{!}} Don Bosco High School |url=https://donboscomatunga.com/alumni/notable-alumni/ |website=donboscomatunga.com}}</ref> simultaneously learning [[Karate]].  He enrolled in [[Guru Nanak Khalsa College of Arts, Science & Commerce|Guru Nanak Khalsa College]] for higher education, but dropped out as he was not much interested in studies. He requested his father that he wanted to learn martial arts further, and his father somehow saved money to send him to Thailand. Kumar went to [[Bangkok]] to learn [[martial arts]] and lived in Thailand for five years learning [[Thai Boxing]].<ref name="HTMKhalid" /><ref>{{cite news|last1=Gupta|first1=Priya|title=I've got more than what I had ever dreamt of: Akshay Kumar|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Ive-got-more-than-what-I-had-ever-dreamt-of-Akshay-Kumar/articleshow/21776783.cms|accessdate=19 August 2015|work=[[The Times of India]]|publisher=[[The Times Group]]|date=13 August 2013}}</ref> Kumar also has a sister, Alka Bhatia.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ndtv.com/photos/entertainment/akshay-twinkle-at-pre-karva-chauth-bash-8460 |title=Akshay, Twinkle at pre-Karva Chauth bash|publisher=[[NDTV]]|accessdate=9 March 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130524134015/http://www.ndtv.com/photos/entertainment/akshay-twinkle-at-pre-karva-chauth-bash-8460|archivedate=24 May 2013}}</ref> When Kumar was a teenager, his father asked him what he aspired to be. Kumar expressed his desire to become an actor.<ref>{{cite news|title=Unplugged: Akshay Kumar|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/life-style/people/Unplugged-Akshay-Kumar/articleshow/4328069.cms|work=[[The Times of India]]|publisher=[[The Times Group]]|accessdate=9 October 2014|date=21 September 2009}}</ref>

After having obtained a [[Black belt (martial arts)|black belt]] in [[Taekwondo]] while in India,<ref name="AS 2012">{{cite web | last=AS | first=Sashidhar | title=Akshay obtained a black belt in Taekwondo | website=The Times of India | date=8 September 2012 | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/did-you-know-/Akshay-obtained-a-black-belt-in-Taekwondo/articleshow/16312135.cms | accessdate=29 November 2015}}</ref> he studied martial arts in [[Bangkok]], Thailand, where he learned [[Muay Thai]] and worked as a chef and waiter.<ref name="Zee News 2015">{{cite web | title=Lesser known facts about Akshay Kumar | website=Zee News | date=8 September 2015 | url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/celebrity/lesser-known-facts-about-akshay-kumar_1668704.html | language=la | accessdate=29 November 2015}}</ref> After Thailand, Kumar went to work in [[Kolkata|Calcutta]] (present-day Kolkata) in a travel agency, in [[Dhaka]] in a hotel and Delhi where he sold Kundan jewellery. Upon his return to Bombay, he commenced the teaching of martial arts.<ref name="rstv" />

During this time, the father of one of his students, himself a model co-ordinator, recommended Kumar into modelling which ultimately led to a modelling assignment for a furniture showroom. Kumar effectively made more money within the first two days of shooting than in his entire month's salary, and therefore chose a modelling career path. He worked as an assistant for photographer [[Jayesh Sheth]] for 18 months without payment to shoot his first portfolio.<ref>{{cite news|title=Akshay before he became a star|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2009/jan/07slide1-jayesh-on-akshay-kumar.htm|accessdate=5 May 2016|publisher=Rediff.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author1=Upala KBR|title=There and back again for Akshay|url=http://www.mid-day.com/articles/there-and-back-again-for-akshay/98013|accessdate=5 May 2016|work=mid-day|date=12 October 2010}}</ref> He also worked as a background dancer in various films.<ref>{{cite news|title=So what if I play Akshay Kumar's dad?: Jackie Shroff|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-so-what-if-i-play-akshay-kumar-s-dad-jackie-shroff-2024216|accessdate=6 November 2014|work=[[Daily News and Analysis]]|publisher=Diligent Media Corporation|date=8 October 2014|location=Mumbai}}</ref> One morning, he missed his flight for an ad-shoot in Bangalore. Disappointed with himself, he visited a film studio along with his portfolio. That evening, Kumar was signed for a lead role by producer Pramod Chakravarthy for the movie ''[[Deedar (1992 film)|Deedar]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Verma|first1=Sukanya|title=Star of the Week – Akshay Kumar|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2002/nov/20list.htm|publisher=[[Rediff.com]]|accessdate=29 July 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140809104524/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2002/nov/20list.htm|archivedate=9 August 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Singh|first1=Prashant|title=Karisma Kapoor is Akshay Kumar's lucky charm?|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/karisma-kapoor-is-akshay-kumar-s-lucky-charm/article1-1171327.aspx|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|accessdate=29 July 2014|location=Mumbai|date=10 January 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140405101732/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/karisma-kapoor-is-akshay-kumar-s-lucky-charm/article1-1171327.aspx|archivedate=5 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Singh|first1=Prashant|title=Akshay Kumar offers to act in student's film|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/akshay-kumar-offers-to-act-in-student-s-film/article1-885198.aspx|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|accessdate=29 July 2014|location=Mumbai|date=8 July 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120812102655/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/Akshay-Kumar-offers-to-act-in-student-s-film/Article1-885198.aspx|archivedate=12 August 2012}}</ref>

