[[File:Launch of the song 'Taang Uthake' from the film Housefull 3.jpg|thumb|right|upright=1.4|Kumar with his Housefull series co-star [[Jacqueline Fernandez]].]]
His first release of 2012 was ''[[Housefull 2]]'', a sequel of his earlier comedy film ''Housefull''. The film received mixed reviews from critics but was very successful at the box office.<ref>{{cite web|title=Housefull 2 Crosses 400 Crore Nett in 17 days|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4327&nCat=|publisher=Box Office India|accessdate=6 September 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131106102719/http://boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4327&nCat=|archivedate=6 November 2013}}</ref> It was also a huge hit in overseas market and the biggest [[Bollywood]] grosser in New Zealand.<ref>{{cite news|title=Housefull 2 Is All Time Blockbuster in New Zealand|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/npages.php?page=shownews&articleid=4364&nCat=|publisher=Box Office India|accessdate=6 September 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120626143416/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/npages.php?page=shownews&articleid=4364&nCat=|archivedate=26 June 2012|date=30 April 2012}}</ref> Kumar's next film was the [[Prabhudeva]]-directed action drama ''[[Rowdy Rathore]]'' in which he played a double role opposite [[Sonakshi Sinha]].<ref name="hindustantimes1">{{cite news| url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/Rowdy-Rathore-gets-thumbs-up-from-critics/Article1-864444.aspx |work=[[Hindustan Times]] |title= Rowdy Rathore gets thumbs up from critics| date=1 June 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120602064158/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/Rowdy-Rathore-gets-thumbs-up-from-critics/Article1-864444.aspx|archivedate=2 June 2012}}</ref> The film earned more than {{INRConvert|1.3|b}} in India and was a huge box office success, being declared a "blockbuster". Both of these films grossed over {{INRconvert|1|b}} at the box office.<ref>{{cite news|title=Barfi! joins INR1&nbsp;billion club|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/446981/barfi-joins-inr1-billion-club/|work=[[The Express Tribune]]|publisher=[[Lakson Group]]|accessdate=29 July 2014|date=4 October 2012}}</ref> Although the former film received mixed reviews; Kumar's performance in it was praised.<ref>{{cite news|title=Housefull 2: Times of India Review|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/movie-review/12544440.cms|work=[[The Times of India]]|publisher=[[The Times Group]]|accessdate=30 July 2014|date=6 April 2012}}</ref> In 2012, he founded another production company called Grazing Goat Pictures Pvt Ltd.<ref>{{cite news|title=Akshay Kumar gets a Grazing Goat|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news-interviews/Akshay-Kumar-gets-a-Grazing-Goat/articleshow/10901424.cms|work=[[The Times of India]]|publisher=[[The Times Group]]|accessdate=17 June 2014|date=28 November 2011}}</ref>
[[Joker (2012 film)|Joker]] was reportedly promoted as Kumar's 100th film,<ref>{{cite news| url=http://ibnlive.in.com/photogallery/6933.html|title= First Look: Akshay Kumar's 100th film 'Joker'|publisher=[[CNN-IBN]] |date=11 July 2012|accessdate=22 November 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131208202123/http://ibnlive.in.com/photogallery/6933.html|archivedate=8 December 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/joker-trailer-to-release-with-cocktail-news-bollywood-mhirugfffdf.html?ref=false/ |title=Joker trailer to release with Cocktail |publisher=[[Sify]] |date=9 July 2012 |accessdate=22 November 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140124223124/http://www.sify.com/movies/joker-trailer-to-release-with-cocktail-news-bollywood-mhirugfffdf.html |archivedate=24 January 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.mid-day.com/entertainment/2012/jul/090712-Joker-trailer-to-release-with-Cocktail.htm/ | title ='Joker' trailer to release with 'Cocktail' | work =[[Mid Day]] |date=9 July 2012|accessdate=22 November 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120710075757/http://www.mid-day.com/entertainment/2012/jul/090712-Joker-trailer-to-release-with-Cocktail.htm|archivedate=10 July 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://post.jagran.com/akshay-kumars-joker-trailer-to-release-with-saifs-cocktail-1341827526| title = Akshay Kumar's 'Joker' trailer to release with Saif's 'Cocktail'| work =Jagran |date=9 July 2012|accessdate=22 November 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131208004450/http://post.jagran.com/akshay-kumars-joker-trailer-to-release-with-saifs-cocktail-1341827526|archivedate=8 December 2013}}</ref> but later Akshay Kumar clarified that the 100th film landmark had been crossed long before he even signed up for Joker. "It was a miscalculation on Shirish's part. [[Oh My God (2012 film)|OMG]] is my 116th film," he said.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/channels/showbiz/bollywood/akki%E2%80%99s-back-game-842 |title=Akki's back in the game |date=19 September 2012 |work=[[Deccan Chronicle]]|publisher=Deccan Chronicle Holdings|accessdate=19 September 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120920002835/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/channels/showbiz/bollywood/akki%E2%80%99s-back-game-842|archivedate=20 September 2012}}</ref> Kumar kept himself away from the film's promotion due to differences with Kunder. Reacting to Kumar's backing out from the film's promotion Kunder tweeted "A true leader takes responsibility for his team and leads them through thick and thin. Never abandons them and runs away." He later deleted the tweet.<ref>{{cite news|title=Top 5 Reasons: Why Akshay Kumar fell out with Shirish Kunder|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/top-5-reasons-why-akshay-kumar-fell-out-with-shirish-kunder/article1-922431.aspx|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|accessdate=23 August 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130603073319/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/TOP-5-REASONS-Why-Akshay-Kumar-fell-out-with-Shirish-Kunder/Article1-922431.aspx|archivedate=3 June 2013|location=New Delhi|date=31 August 2012}}</ref> His later release ''[[OMG: Oh My God!|Oh My God]]'' which he produced and starred along with [[Paresh Rawal]].<ref name="hindustantimes1" /> It had a slow opening but because of word of mouth it picked up and then was declared a super hit.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/cpages.php?pageName=earnings|title=Box Office Earnings 28/09/12 – 04/10/12|publisher=Box Office India|accessdate=22 November 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131109170539/http://boxofficeindia.com/cpages.php?pageName=earnings |archivedate=9 November 2013 }}</ref>

His last release in 2012 was ''[[Khiladi 786]]'', the eighth instalment in his famous ''Khiladi'' series as well as the comeback of the series after 12 years. Although film was panned by critics it was a Semihit at the box office grossing 700&nbsp;million at domestic box office.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koimoi.com/box-office-bollywood-films-of-2012/ |title=Box-Office Verdicts of Major Bollywood Releases of 2012|publisher=[[Koimoi]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120630063337/http://www.koimoi.com/box-office-bollywood-films-of-2012/|archivedate=30 June 2012}}</ref> His first release in 2013 was ''[[Special Chabbis]]'' which earned a positive critical reception and was moderately successful at the box office. Although the movie earned him positive reviews and commercial success, trade analysts noted that the movie could have done much better business due to its good content and Kumar's high-profile. [[Milan Luthria]] chose Kumar to play the character of Shoaib Khan (based on [[Dawood Ibrahim]]) in the [[gangster film]] ''[[Once Upon ay Time in Mumbai Dobaara!]]'', sequel to ''[[Once Upon a Time in Mumbaai]]''. It proved to be a below average at the box office. The film was declared a "flop" by [[Box Office India]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Satyagraha Average Opening Chennai Express Hits 200 Crore|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=6017&nCat=|publisher=Box Office India|accessdate=6 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130903073357/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=6017&nCat=|archivedate=3 September 2013}}</ref> It received mixed reviews however Kumar's acting was praised by a majority of critics. In a review for ''[[Hindustan Times]]'', [[Anupama Chopra]] wrote that Kumar "makes a stellar killer".<ref>{{cite news|first=Anupama|last=Chopra|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/reviews/anupama-chopra-s-review-once-upon-a-time-in-mumbaai-dobaara/article1-1108821.aspx |title=Anupama Chopra's review: Once Upon A Time In Mumbaai Dobaara!|work= [[Hindustan Times]] |date=16 August 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130817121535/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Reviews/Anupama-Chopra-s-review-Once-Upon-A-Time-In-Mumbaai-Dobaara/Article1-1108821.aspx|archivedate=17 August 2013}}</ref> Madhureeta Mukherjee of ''[[The Times of India]]'' praised Kumar's performance and said that "''Bhai'' act with flamboyance and mojo ... He gets a chance to do what he does best – ''herogiri'' (albeit less menacing, more entertaining), with charisma and clap-trap dialoguebaazi."<ref>{{cite news|first=Madhureeta |last=Mukherjee|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/hindi/Once-Upon-Ay-Time-In-Mumbai-Dobaara/movie-review/21820641.cms |title=Once Upon Ay Time in Mumbai Dobaara! : Movie Review|work= [[The Times of India]] |publisher=[[The Times Group]]|date=15 August 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130815094643/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/hindi/Once-Upon-Ay-Time-In-Mumbai-Dobaara/movie-review/21820641.cms|archivedate=15 August 2013}}</ref> [[Al Pacino]] saw the film's trailer and promos and admired Kumar's portrayal of Shoaib Khan, a gangster. He said that the promos and posters reminded him of his own ''[[The Godfather]]''. Kumar said of Pacino's response: "A touch of appreciation is always held dearly in an actor's arms, even if it's from the simplest of people like our beloved spot boys. But to have your work spoken of so kindly by the world's most admired gangster Al Pacino himself – I had goose-bumps thinking about him watching the promo! I was so humbled, not only as an actor but as a fan of his legendary work."<ref>{{cite news|last1=Das|first1=Anirban|title=Al Pacino praises Akshay Kumar's work|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/movies/al-pacino-praises-akshay-kumar-s-work/article1-1099759.aspx|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|accessdate=6 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140518004546/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/movies/al-pacino-praises-akshay-kumar-s-work/article1-1099759.aspx|archivedate=18 May 2014|location=New Delhi|date=28 July 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Bollywood Hungama News Network|title=Al Pacino's thumbs up to Once Upon Ay Time in Mumbaai Dobaara|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/1946833/al-pacino|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=6 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131224114843/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/1946833/al-pacino|archivedate=24 December 2013|date=29 July 2013}}</ref> Rajeev Masand of [[CNN-IBN]] criticised Kumar for his "in-your-face flamboyance".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Masand|first1=Rajeev|title='Once Upon Ay Time in Mumbai Dobaara' review: It is like getting a root canal|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/once-upon-ay-time-in-mumbai-dobaara-review-it-is-like-getting-a-root-canal/414577-47-84.html|publisher=[[CNN-IBN]]|accessdate=6 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714010054/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/once-upon-ay-time-in-mumbai-dobaara-review-it-is-like-getting-a-root-canal/414577-47-84.html|archivedate=14 July 2014}}</ref> After the film's mainly negative reviews, Kumar lashed out at critics, accusing them of lacking an understanding of the audience and the basic ideas of filmmaking.<ref>{{cite news|title=Akshay Kumar breathes fury at Once Upon A Time in Mumbai Dobaara critics|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/akshay-kumar-wakes-up-decides-to-breathe-fury-at-ouatimd-critics/1/300772.html|work=[[India Today]]|location=New Delhi|accessdate=6 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203002345/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/akshay-kumar-wakes-up-decides-to-breathe-fury-at-ouatimd-critics/1/300772.html|archivedate=3 December 2013|date=22 August 2013}}</ref> Built on an approximate budget of {{INRConvert|1|b}},<ref>{{cite news|author1=Indo-Asian News Service|authorlink1=Indo-Asian News Service|title=Once Upon Ay Time in Mumbai Dobaara: Another film to hit the jackpot?|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/once-upon-ay-time-in-mumbai-dobaara-another-film-to-hit-the-jackpot/414267-8-66.html|publisher=[[CNN-IBN]]|accessdate=6 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029025141/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/once-upon-ay-time-in-mumbai-dobaara-another-film-to-hit-the-jackpot/414267-8-66.html|archivedate=29 October 2013|location=New Delhi|date=14 August 2013}}</ref> it was the first major [[Hindi]] language film to be shot in [[Oman]].<ref>{{cite news|author1=Times News Network|title=Once Upon sequel – first film shot in exotic Oman|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Once-Upon-sequel-first-film-shot-in-exotic-Oman/articleshow/16722103.cms|work=[[The Times of India]]|publisher=[[The Times Group]]|accessdate=6 October 2014|date=8 October 2012}}</ref> Kumar received a nomination for Best Actor in a Negative Role at [[Zee Cine Awards]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mudi|first1=Aparna|title=Zee Cine Awards 2014: Complete list of nominations|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/zee-cine-awards-2014/zee-cine-awards-2014-complete-list-of-nominations_150384.html|publisher=[[Zee News]]|accessdate=18 October 2014|date=6 February 2014}}</ref>

His next release was Anthony D Souza's ''[[Boss (2013 Hindi film)|Boss]]'' alongside [[Shiv Panditt]] and [[Aditi Rao Hydari]]. The movie received average to good reviews<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/566663 |title=Boss: Critic Review|publisher=Bollywood Hungama |date=15 August 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131020050454/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/566663|archivedate=20 October 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Review: Akshay Kumar's Boss: All title, no thunder!|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-akshay-kumars-boss-all-title-no-thunder/20131016.htm|publisher=[[Rediff.com]]|accessdate=17 June 2014|date=16 October 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/movie-review-boss-is-all-about-masala-and-akshay-kumar/article1-1135845.aspx |title=Movie review: Boss is all about masala and Akshay Kumar |work=[[Hindustan Times]]  |date=16 October 2013 |accessdate=31 July 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140808060318/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/movie-review-boss-is-all-about-masala-and-akshay-kumar/article1-1135845.aspx |archivedate=8 August 2014 }}</ref> however turned out to be a failure at Box office grossing 54&nbsp;crore nett domestically.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.koimoi.com/box-office-bollywood-films-of-2013/ |title=Box-Office Verdict 2013-Box Office Collection of all 2013 Releases|publisher=[[Koimoi]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140803012622/http://www.koimoi.com/box-office-bollywood-films-of-2013/|archivedate=3 August 2014}}</ref> Kumar came back strongly with ''[[Holiday: A Soldier Is Never Off Duty]]'', the Hindi remake of the 2012 Tamil film ''[[Thuppakki]]''. This action drama earned both critical and commercial success entering the 1&nbsp;billion elite club and became the highest grosser of 2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=Akshay's Holiday Beats Lifetime Collections of Salman's Jai Ho|url=http://www.koimoi.com/box-office/akshay-holiday-beats-lifetime-collections-of-salmans-jai-ho/|publisher=[[Koimoi]]|accessdate=23 August 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140804105938/http://www.koimoi.com/box-office/akshay-holiday-beats-lifetime-collections-of-salmans-jai-ho/|archivedate=4 August 2014|date=29 June 2014}}</ref> The film received critical acclaim and is Kumar's third film to gross over {{INRconvert|1|b|nolink=yes}} at the box office.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Bawa |first1=Jyoti Sharma |title=Akshay impresses in Holiday's action sequences |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/reviews/movie-review-akshay-kumar-s-holiday-will-keep-you-hooked/article1-1226341.aspx |work=[[Hindustan Times]]  |accessdate=18 June 2014 |date=14 June 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140617060035/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/reviews/movie-review-akshay-kumar-s-holiday-will-keep-you-hooked/article1-1226341.aspx |archivedate=17 June 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-review/holiday-a-soldier-is-never-off-duty/movie-review/36099137.cms|title=Holiday – A Soldier Is Never Off Duty|work=[[The Times of India]]|publisher=[[The Times Group]]|date=5 June 2014|accessdate=31 July 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Holiday-enters-the-100-crore-club/articleshow/37018014.cms|title=Holiday enters the 100 crore club!|work=[[The Times of India]]|publisher=[[The Times Group]]|date=23 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/akshay-kumar-s-holiday-to-enter-rs-100-crore-club/article1-1228347.aspx |title=Akshay Kumar's Holiday one of the biggest hits of 2014 |work=[[Hindustan Times]]  |date=11 June 2014 |accessdate=31 July 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140729071146/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/akshay-kumar-s-holiday-to-enter-rs-100-crore-club/article1-1228347.aspx |archivedate=29 July 2014 }}</ref> Kumar has sung a song for his recent film ''[[Entertainment (2014 film)|It's Entertainment]]''. Making of the song has been uploaded on YouTube.<ref>{{cite news|title=Akshay Kumar sings for 'Entertainment'|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/watch-akshay-kumar-sings-for-entertainment/|work=[[The Indian Express]]|publisher=[[Indian Express Group]]|accessdate=23 August 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140823032632/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/watch-akshay-kumar-sings-for-entertainment/|archivedate=23 August 2014|location=Mumbai|date=27 July 2014}}</ref> His last film of 2014 was ''[[The Shaukeens]]''. He appeared as himself and produced it.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Tarannum|first1=Asira|title=Akshay Kumar doesn't want to over-promote himself for 'The Shaukeens'|url=http://www.mid-day.com/articles/akshay-kumar-doesnt-want-to-over-promote-himself-for-the-shaukeens/15639156|accessdate=1 May 2015|work=[[Mid Day]]|date=27 September 2014}}</ref> He played the lead role in the thriller ''[[Baby (2015 Hindi film)|Baby]]'' and ''[[Gabbar is Back]]''.<ref>{{cite news|author1=Press Trust of India|title=Akshay Kumar's 'Baby' trailer released|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/akshay-kumars-baby-trailer-released/|accessdate=1 May 2015|work=The Indian Express|publisher=Indian Express Group|date=4 December 2014|location=Mumbai}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Watch: Sholay style teaser of Akshay Kumar's 'Gabbar Is Back'|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-watch-sholay-style-teaser-of-akshay-kumar-s-gabbar-is-back-2068549|accessdate=1 May 2015|work=Daily News and Analysis|publisher=Diligent Media Corporation|date=13 March 2015|location=Mumbai}}</ref> Kumar's first collaboration with [[Karan Johar]], ''[[Brothers (2015 film)|Brothers]]'' was released on 14 August 2015.<ref>{{cite news|author1=Indo-Asian News Service|title=Akshay Kumar wraps up 'Brothers' shooting|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/akshay-kumar-wraps-up-brothers-shooting/articleshow/46969888.cms|accessdate=1 May 2015|work=The Economic Times|date=18 April 2015|location=Mumbai}}</ref> His next release was ''[[Singh is Bling]]'' was released on 2 October 2015 and is produced by Grazing Goats Pictures.<ref>[http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/akshay-kumars-singh-is-bliing-mints-rs-54-44-crore-in-three-days/ Akshay Kumar’s ‘Singh is Bliing’ mints Rs.54.44 crore in three days]. [[The Indian Express]]. 5 October 2015</ref>

=== 2016–present ===
His first release was ''[[Airlift]]'' released on 22 January 2016 was critically and commercially successful,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Dani|first1=Arti|title=Akshay Kumar shooting in Ras Al Khaimah|url=http://www.khaleejtimes.com/citytimes/inside.asp?xfile=/data/citytimes/2015/April/citytimes_April6.xml&section=citytimes|accessdate=1 May 2015|work=[[Khaleej Times]]|publisher=[[Galadari Printing and Publishing]]|date=2 April 2015|location=Dubai}}</ref> and second ''[[Housefull 3]]'' was released on 3 June 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=Akshay, Riteish, Abhishek begin shooting Housefull 3|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Akshay-Riteish-Abhishek-begin-shooting-Housefull-3/articleshow/48511330.cms|work=The Times of India|agency=Press Trust of India|accessdate=6 October 2015|date=17 August 2015}}</ref> ''Namastey England'', sequel to ''Namastey London'' has been announced.<ref>{{cite news|title=Akshay Kumar in 'Namaste London' sequel, titled 'Namaste England'|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-akshay-kumar-in-namaste-london-sequel-titled-namaste-england-2096157|accessdate=19 August 2015|work=Daily News and Analysis|publisher=Diligent Media Corporation|date=16 June 2015}}</ref> ''[[Rustom (film)|Rustom]]'' which was produced by Neeraj Pandey and marked his 3rd release of 2016. Akshay was praised for his performance in Rustom which garnered him numerous award nominations. Rustom grossed more than 2&nbsp;billion at the box office.<ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Akshay-Kumar-s-romantic-thriller-Rustom-to-release-on-I-Day-weekend/articleshow/48884569.cms Akshay Kumar 's romantic thriller ‘Rustom’ to release on I-Day weekend – The Times of India]. ''The Times of India''. (9 September 2015). Retrieved 29 September 2015.</ref> Both ''Airlift'' and ''Rustom'' earned him the [[National Film Award for Best Actor]].<ref name="NFA">{{cite news|last=Jha|first1=Subhash K.|title=Akshay Won National Award For 'Rustom' & 'Airlift': Priyadarshan|url=https://www.thequint.com/entertainment/bollywood/akshay-kumar-won-national-award-for-both-rustom-and-airlift-says-priyadarshan |accessdate=19 February 2019|work=[[The Quint]]|date=7 April 2017}}</ref>

His only film release in 2017 was ''[[Toilet: Ek Prem Katha]]''. This film depicted the serious of issue of Toilets in certain regions of the country. Akshay's performance was praised. Akshay Kumar dug a toilet in [[Madhya Pradesh]] to promote the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://santabantawallpaper.co.in/toilet-ek-prem-katha|title=Akshay Kumar Toilet ek Prem katha first look, HD Wallpapers story, star cast, released date|website=santabantawallpaper.co.in|accessdate=30 July 2017|date=11 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170719151145/http://santabantawallpaper.co.in/toilet-ek-prem-katha|archive-date=19 July 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> The movie trailer was released on 11 June 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.missmahi.com/movie/wiki/toilet-ek-prem-katha-wiki-star-cast-release-date/8908/|title=Toilet Ek Prem Katha Wiki, Star Cast & Release Date|date=12 June 2017|work=MissMahi|access-date=12 June 2017}}</ref> PM Modi called it a good effort to further the message of cleanliness, as per [[Swachh Bharat Abhiyan]].<ref>{{cite news|title=PM Narendra Modi Lauds Akshay Kumar Toilet Ek Prem Katha's Trailer; Calls It a Good Effort to Further the Message of Cleanliness|url=http://www.news18.com/news/movies/pm-narendra-modi-lauds-akshay-kumar-toilet-ek-prem-katha-trailer-calls-it-a-good-effort-to-further-the-message-of-cleanliness-1430809.html|publisher=News18|date=13 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=PM Narendra Modi impressed with Akshay Kumar's 'Toilet Ek Prem Katha' trailer|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/pm-modi-impressed-with-akshay-kumars-toilet-ek-prem-katha-trailer/articleshow/59123054.cms|work=[[The Times of India]]|date=12 June 2017}}</ref>

In 2018, Akshay starred in the social drama film ''[[Pad Man (film)|Pad Man]]'' alongside [[Sonam Kapoor]] and [[Radhika Apte]].<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/akshay-kumars-next-r-balki-titled-pad-man/ |title = Pad man Official Theatrical Trailer |date = 15 December 2017|work = Bollywood Hungama|access-date = 23 December 2017}}</ref> He later made his [[Tamil cinema]] debut in the science fiction thriller ''[[2.0 (film)|2.0]]'', co-starring [[Rajinikanth]], in which he played an evil ornithologist named Pakshirajan.<ref name="TOI">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Akshay-Kumar-plays-the-villain-in-Robot-2/articleshow/50203162.cms|title=Akshay Kumar plays the villain in 'Robot 2'|work=The Times of India}}</ref><ref name="TH2.0">{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/rajinikanths-20-first-look-to-be-out-on-november-20/article9206701.ece|title=Rajinikanth's 2.0 first look to be out on November 20|newspaper=The Hindu|date=10 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/2.0-is-set-to-go-where-no-Indian-film-has-gone-before/article16738922.ece|title=2.0 is set to go where no Indian film has gone before|last=Bureau|first=City|work=The Hindu|access-date=13 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Rajnikanth's 2.0 vs Aamir Khan's Thugs of Hindostan – There Could Be A Clash This Diwali!|url=https://in.bookmyshow.com/entertainment-news/movies/bollywood/rajnikanths-2-0-vs-aamir-khans-thugs-hindostan-clash-diwali|website=BookMyShow|accessdate=27 February 2018}}</ref>

In 2019, Kumar appeared in [[Karan Johar]]'s film ''[[Kesari (film)|Kesari]]'' opposite [[Parineeti Chopra]], based on the story of the Battle of Saragarhi. The film grossed over {{INRConvert|200|c|}} worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/box-office-collections/worldwide/2019/|title=Bollywood Top Grossers Worldwide Bollywood Hungama|access-date=20 April 2019|website=Bollywood Hungama}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/breaking-parineeti-chopra-signed-opposite-akshay-kumar-karan-johars-kesari/ |title = BREAKING: Parineeti Chopra signed opposite Akshay Kumar for Karan Johar's Kesari|date = 10 January 2018|work = Bollywood Hungama|access-date = 11 January 2018}}</ref> He is featuring in ''[[Mission Mangal]]'' with an ensemble cast of [[Vidya Balan]], [[Taapsee Pannu]], [[Nithya Menen]], [[Sharman Joshi]] and [[Sonakshi Sinha]]. The film is about the story of scientists at [[Indian Space Research Organisation]] who contributed to the [[Mars Orbiter Mission]], which marked India's first interplanetary expedition.<ref>{{cite news|title=Akshay Kumar's Mission Mangal will star Vidya Balan, Taapsee Pannu, Nithya Menen, Sonakshi Sinha, Manish Borundia|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/akshay-kumar-signs-three-new-projects-to-start-shooting-for-mission-mangal-this-month/story-SJRWDHneqcNvDEBRBgHXMO.html|work=Hindustan Times|accessdate=5 November 2018|date=5 November 2018}}</ref> ''[[Housefull 4]]'', directed by [[Sajid-Farhad|Farhad Samji]], was released in October 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last=Basu |first=Nilanjana|title=Housefull 4 Begins. Akshay Kumar, Bobby Deol, Riteish Deshmukh Have A Warning For You |url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/housefull-4-begins-akshay-kumar-bobby-deol-riteish-deshmukh-have-a-warning-for-you-1880629 |website=NDTV |accessdate=29 August 2018  |date=10 July 2018 }}</ref> His next release in December 2019 was [[Karan Johar]]'s and his own production ''[[Good Newwz]]'', a [[romantic comedy]] about [[surrogacy]], opposite [[Kareena Kapoor Khan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-good-news-that-s-the-title-of-kareena-kapoor-khan-s-next-with-akshay-kumar-here-s-what-the-film-is-all-about-2643923/amp?|title='Good News'! That's the title of Kareena Kapoor Khan's next with Akshay Kumar|date=31 July 2018|publisher= DNA India|accessdate=14 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title='Good Newwz' box office collection Day 3: Akshay Kumar and Kareena Kapoor Khan starrer witnesses a good Sunday - Times of India |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/box-office/good-newwz-box-office-collection-day-3-akshay-kumar-and-kareena-kapoor-khan-starrer-witnesses-a-good-sunday/articleshow/73024282.cms |accessdate=31 December 2019 |work=The Times of India |date=30 December 2019 |language=en}}</ref>

