==Personal life and off-screen work==
[[File:Akshay Kumar with family.jpg|thumb|right| Kumar with his wife [[Twinkle Khanna]] (left) and mother-in-law, [[Dimple Kapadia]] (right).]]

After being engaged twice to actress [[Twinkle Khanna]], the daughter of actors [[Rajesh Khanna]] and [[Dimple Kapadia]], Kumar married her on 17 January 2001. Together they have a son,  and a daughter.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Tabloid/CONGRATS-Akshay-Kumar-Twinkle-Khanna-blessed-with-a-baby-girl/Article1-935239.aspx|title=CONGRATS! Akshay Kumar-Twinkle Khanna blessed with a baby girl|work=[[Hindustan Times]] |accessdate=25 September 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120925195430/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Tabloid/CONGRATS-Akshay-Kumar-Twinkle-Khanna-blessed-with-a-baby-girl/Article1-935239.aspx|archivedate=25 September 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-06-18/news-interviews/32298040_1_twinkle-akshay-kumar-aarav | archive-url=https://archive.is/20120715063233/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-06-18/news-interviews/32298040_1_twinkle-akshay-kumar-aarav | url-status=dead | archive-date=15 July 2012 | title= Akshay, Twinkle set to welcome their second child| date=18 June 2012 |work=[[The Times of India]]|publisher=[[The Times Group]]}}</ref> He is known as a protective father and keeps his children away from the media. He stated that he wants to "give them a normal childhood."<ref>{{cite news|title=Better to keep children away from limelight, says Akshay Kumar|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/akshay-kumar-children-limelight-holiday-father/1/367011.html|work=[[India Today]]|accessdate=21 August 2014|location=Mumbai|date=15 June 2014}}</ref> In 2009, while performing at a show for Levis at Lakme Fashion Week, Kumar asked Twinkle to unbutton his jeans. This incident sparked a controversy which led to a police case being filed against them.<ref name="HTOTY">{{cite news|last=Marwah |first=Navdeep Kaur |title=Over The Years: The rise of Mr Khiladi |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/over-the-years-the-rise-of-mr-khiladi/article1-934443.aspx |work=[[Hindustan Times]]  |accessdate=22 August 2014 |location=New Delhi |date=23 September 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131027093350/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/OVER-THE-YEARS-The-rise-of-Mr-Khiladi/Article1-934443.aspx |archivedate=27 October 2013 }}</ref>

Kumar stays in shape with a combination of kickboxing, basketball, swimming and [[Parkour]] as well as working out. While in standard eighth he had started practising Karate. He intended to open a martial arts school and the state government of [[Maharashtra]] allotted land for the school in Bhayandar.<ref name="Bhayandar">{{cite news|last=Ruhani|first=Faheem|title=Akshay Kumar lends glamour to kabaddi, buys a team|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/akshay-kumar-kabaddi-buys-team-maharashtra-government-world-kabaddi-league/1/367298.html|work=[[India Today]]|accessdate=21 August 2014|date=17 June 2014}}</ref> In 2004, he was honoured with the Rajiv Gandhi Award for his outstanding achievements in Bollywood. In the same year, he presented the television series ''[[Seven Deadly Arts with Akshay Kumar]]'' for free.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Fernandes|first1=Vivek|title=Akshay Kumar: Winning hearts with martial arts!|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2004/apr/26akshay.htm|accessdate=6 November 2014|publisher=Rediff.com|date=26 April 2004|location=Mumbai}}</ref>The following year Kumar was awarded the highest Japanese honour of "Katana" and a sixth degree [[Black belt (martial arts)|black belt]] in Kuyukai [[Gōjū-ryū]] karate. 
[[File:Akshay Kumar with his wife Twinkle Khanna in 2015.jpg|thumb|left|upright=1.2|Kumar with his wife [[Twinkle Khanna]] at the launch of ''[[Mrs Funnybones]]'' in 2015]] 

Kumar was initially a religious, practising [[Shaiva]] [[Hindu]] who regularly visited shrines and temples across the country, including the famed [[Vaishno Devi Mandir]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.indiawest.com/entertainment/bollywood/interviews/akshay-kumar-on-gabbar-is-back-i-have-a-great/article_8b2b61f8-f054-11e4-a4e5-7f162b79a4f6.html |title=Akshay Kumar Proclaims He's A 'Shiv Bhakt' As Well As His Grandfather |date=1 May 2015 |work=India-West |access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/pic-akshay-kumar-signs-mogul-at-the-lord-shiva-temple-in-maheshwar/amp_articleshow/57988782.cms |title=Pic: Akshay Kumar signs 'Mogul' at the Lord Shiva temple in Maheshwar |date=3 April 2017 |website=The Times of India |access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/maha-shivratri-akshay-kumar-tweeted-the-best-shiva-message-we-are-already-sending-it-to-friends-4541225/lite/ |title=Maha Shivaratri: Akshay Kumar tweeted the best Shiva message. We are already sending it to friends |date=24 February 2017 |work=The Indian Express |access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref><ref name="m.mid-day.com">{{Cite news |url=https://m.mid-day.com/amp/articles/bollywood-news-akshay-kumar-mandir-temple-true-meaning-social-messages-films/18216155 |title=Akshay Kumar reveals what he feels is the true meaning of 'mandir' |date=2 May 2017 |work=Mid-Day |access-date=11 March 2020 |agency=IANS}}</ref> but in March 2020 he stated, "I don’t believe in any religion. I only believe in being Indian".<ref>{{cite news |title=Akshay Kumar: 'I don't believe in any religion, I only believe in being Indian' |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/akshay-kumar-i-don-t-believe-in-any-religion-i-only-believe-in-being-indian/story-U9w2JZxQVa84iTidAhLGDJ.html |accessdate=10 March 2020 |work=[[Hindustan Times]] |agency=[[Press Trust of India]] |date=8 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref> He is a [[Teetotalism|teetotaller]] but has endorsed for a liquor brand in the past. Half of the sum was given for ''[[dāna|daan]]'' (charity work), of which he has been doing more of in recent times.<ref name="m.mid-day.com" /> He has also donated {{INRConvert|5|m}} to [[Salman Khan]]'s Being Human Foundation.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Thakkar|first1=Mehul S|title=Teetotaller Akshay endorses alcohol but for 'charity'|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Teetotaller-Akshay-endorses-alcohol-but-for-charity/articleshow/17304750.cms|accessdate=6 November 2014|work=[[The Times of India]]|publisher=[[The Times Group]]|date=21 November 2012|location=Mumbai}}</ref><!--  In 2013, one of his fan travelled from [[Haryana]] to Mumbai, to meet him. The journey took him 42 days. When he reached Kumar's building, he was informed that Kumar was in Casablanca. The fan stayed outside the building for one week before Kumar met him.<ref>{{cite news|title=An Akshay Kumar fan walked for 42 days from Haryana to Mumbai to meet the actor|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-an-akshay-kumar-fan-walked-for-42-days-from-haryana-to-mumbai-to-meet-the-actor-1939434|accessdate=6 November 2014|work=[[Daily News and Analysis]]|publisher=Diligent Media Corporation|date=23 December 2013|location=Mumbai}}</ref> --> {{as of|2013}}, Kumar has been the Hindi film industry's highest advance taxpayer for six consecutive years. He paid {{INRConvert|190|m}} as advance tax payment in that year.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Dubey|first1=Bharti|last2=Pandey|first2=Piyush|title=Akshay Kumar Bollywood's top advance taxpayer|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Akshay-Kumar-Bollywoods-top-advance-taxpayer/articleshow/19083337.cms|accessdate=6 November 2014|work=[[The Times of India]]|publisher=[[The Times Group]]|date=20 March 2013|location=Mumbai}}</ref>

On 9 August 2014, Kumar performed at his 500th live show. The show was held in O2 Arena in London as part of the inaugural function of the World Kabaddi League. His first live show was held in 1991 in Delhi. Kumar owns a team in the Kabbadi League.<ref name="Bhayandar" /><ref name="Liveshow">{{cite news|last1=Singh|first1=Prashant|title=Akshay Kumar's 500th live show in London|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/akshay-kumar-s-500th-live-show-in-london/article1-1248791.aspx|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|accessdate=10 August 2014|location=Mumbai|date=6 August 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140807033148/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/akshay-kumar-s-500th-live-show-in-london/article1-1248791.aspx|archivedate=7 August 2014}}</ref> He helped Khanna with editing the drafts of her debut book ''[[Mrs Funnybones]]''.<ref name=TH>{{cite news|author1=Press Trust of India|title=Twinkle Khanna's Mrs Funnybones is now a book|url=http://www.thehindu.com/books/twinkle-khannas-mrs-funnybones-is-now-a-book/article7558757.ece|accessdate=8 September 2015|work=[[The Hindu]]|publisher=[[The Hindu Group]]|date=20 August 2015|location=Mumbai|author1-link=Press Trust of India}}</ref> Kumar also had donated a sum of ₹9&nbsp;million to drought hit farmers in [[Maharashtra]] in 2015.<ref>[http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-what-akshay-kumar-did-for-farmers-will-make-you-salute-him-2130248 What Akshay Kumar did for farmers will make you salute him!]. [[Daily News and Analysis]]. Upala KBR. 30 September 2015</ref><ref>[http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/celebrity/akshay-kumar-lends-a-helping-hand-to-farmers-donates-rs-90-lakhs_1797799.html Akshay Kumar lends a helping hand to farmers, donates ₹90 lakhs]. [[Zee News]]. Gayatri Shankar. 16 September 2015</ref> He has also donated ₹5&nbsp;million to aid drought affected people through the Maharashtra government's Jalyukt Shivar Abhiyan.<ref>{{cite news|title=Maharashtra Drought: Bollywood Actor Akshay Kumar Donates Rs 50 Lakh For The Cause|url=http://www.abplive.in/photos/maharashtra-drought-bollywood-actor-akshay-kumar-donates-rs-50-lakh-for-the-cause-325133|publisher=ABP Live|date=19 April 2016}}</ref>  In March 2013, he started a 30-bed cancer shelter for policemen in [[Naigaon]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Singh|first1=Prashant|title=Akshay Kumar's tribute to his dad|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/tabloid/akshay-kumar-s-tribute-to-his-dad/article1-1026259.aspx|accessdate=6 November 2014|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|date=14 March 2013|location=Mumbai}}</ref><!--  In December 2013, Vishwas Nangre Patil, Additional Commissioner of Police, West Mumbai visited his gym along with several trainee officers.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Gupta|first1=Priya|title=Akshay Kumar trains and impresses real cops|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Akshay-Kumar-trains-and-impresses-real-cops/articleshow/26743004.cms|accessdate=6 November 2014|work=[[The Times of India]]|publisher=[[The Times Group]]|date=3 December 2013}}</ref> -->

On 9 April 2017, Kumar and Union Home Minister [[Rajnath Singh]] promoted a mobile phone app, [[Bharat Ke Veer]], which allows users to donate money to families of people who sacrificed their lives for India. Again on 20 January 2018, he participated in the launch of an Anthem for the initiative. In an event in Delhi he appealed for people to donate to the Bharat Ke Veer cause, and {{INR}}12.93&nbsp;crores was collected.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/akshay-kumar-rajnath-singh-unveil-official-anthem-of-bharat-ke-veer/articleshow/62581609.cms|title=Akshay Kumar, Rajnath Singh unveil official anthem of 'Bharat Ke Veer'|date=20 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/akshay-kumar-s-impromptu-appeal-to-donate-for-bharat-ke-veer-fetches-12-93-crore-in-delhi/story-ygukF36dYaejdXrenxAz5M.html|date=20 January 2018|title=Akshay Kumar's impromptu appeal to donate for Bharat Ke Veer fetches 12.93 crore in Delhi}}</ref>
===Citizenship===
Sometime during or after the [[2011 Canadian federal election]], the [[Conservative Party (Canada)|Conservative]] government there granted Canadian citizenship to Kumar by invoking a little-known law which allowed circumventing the usual residency requirement for Canadian immigrants.<ref name=National-Post-21-May-2019/>  According to a former Conservative Party minister, [[Tony Clement]], the citizenship was awarded in return for Kumar's offer of putting his "star power to use to advance Canada-Indian relations," and Canada's "trade relations, commercial relations, in the movie sector, in the tourism sector."<ref name=National-Post-21-May-2019/>  Although Kumar had earlier appeared in a campaign event for Conservative Prime Minister [[Stephen Harper]] in [[Brampton]], [[Ontario]], a city with a large Indo-Canadian population, and praised Harper, Clement denied that the citizenship was a reward for partisan support.<ref name=National-Post-21-May-2019>{{citation|last=Blackwell|first=Tom|date=21 May 2019|url=https://nationalpost.com/news/politics/bollywood-actor-who-campaigned-for-stephen-harper-was-granted-canadian-citizenship-by-conservative-government|title=Bollywood actor who campaigned for Stephen Harper was granted Canadian citizenship by Conservative government|publisher=National Post|access-date=29 May 2020|quote="In the thick of the 2011 federal election, Stephen Harper appeared in the Indo-Canadian heartland of Ontario with a ringer. At a campaign stop in Brampton, Bollywood mega-star Akshay Kumar praised the then prime minister, danced on stage with his wife, Laureen Harper, and thrilled the audience. And at some point, the Harper government invoked a little-known law to grant the actor Canadian citizenship, circumventing the usual, stringent residency requirements for would-be Canadians, says a former Conservative cabinet minister.  MP Tony Clement, who as industry minister met with Kumar in Mumbai, says the citizenship grant was just a thank you for the actor’s help in promoting Canadian tourism and trade to a huge emerging economy – not a reward for partisan support. 'Basically, he had offered to put that star power to use to advance Canada-India relations, our trade relations, our commercial relations, in the movie sector, in the tourism sector,' said Clement."}}</ref>   Kumar had received an honorary doctorate degree from the [[University of Windsor]], and in a 2010 interview with the ''Economist'' claimed he had "dual citizenship."<ref>{{cite news|title=The Q&A: Akshay Kumar, Bollywood ambassador|url=https://www.economist.com/blogs/prospero/2010/10/indian_cinema|accessdate=23 June 2017|work=The Economist}}</ref>  He was one of the 15 international celebrities invited for the Olympics torch-bearer rally to Canada.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/life-style/health-fitness/fitness/Akshay-Kumars-fitness-mantra/articleshow/9440429.cms |title=Akshay Kumar's fitness mantra |work=[[The Times of India]]|publisher=[[The Times Group]] |date=1 January 1970 |accessdate=2 August 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111224195125/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/life-style/health-fitness/fitness/Akshay-Kumars-fitness-mantra/articleshow/9440429.cms|archivedate=24 December 2011}}</ref> 

In December 2019, Kumar stated that he has applied for an [[Indian passport]] and plans to give up his [[Canadian citizenship]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/movies/celebrities/story/akshay-kumar-i-have-applied-for-an-indian-passport-but-i-am-hurt-that-i-have-to-prove-my-nationality-i-am-indian-to-resume-indian-citizenship-netizens-react-1626096-2019-12-07|title=Akshay Kumar: I've applied for an Indian passport but I'm hurt that I have to prove my nationality|date=7 December 2019|website=India Today|url-status=live|access-date=7 December 2019}}</ref> He stated, "I have now applied for the passport. I am an Indian and it hurts me that I am asked to prove that every time. My wife, my children are Indian. I pay my taxes here and my life is here." Further revealing his reason for earlier changing his nationality as a [[Canadians|Canadian]],  he said," There was a time when I had 14 flops in a row and I was wondering what to do. One of my closest friends who stays in Canada told me come here and we will work together’. I started the process to get a Canadian passport because I felt my career was finished and I won't get more work here. But my 15th film worked and I never looked back. I never thought of changing my passport."<ref name=":0" /><ref name=Passport>{{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/entertainment-news-akshay-kumar-on-canadian-citizenship-got-it-when-i-felt-my-career-was-over-have-applied-for-indian-passport/343730|title=Akshay Kumar On Canadian Citizenship: Got It When I felt My Career Was Over; Have Applied For Indian Passport|last=|first=|date=7 December 2019|website=Outlook India|url-status=live|access-date=7 December 2019}}</ref>

